title: For Sale/Trade:  Red Jacket AK 47, side folder, Krinkov Krink
location: NW San Antonio, San Antonio, Texas
postcontent:
I am looking to sell or trade my Red Jacket built AK 47. For sale for $2,000 obo. That is what I have in it. Here is a description of the gun:

Red Jacket Firearms in Baton Rouge, LA used an unfired, Yugoslavian M92 parts kit and a no dak spud receiver to make this impressive firearm.

Please note, this gun is used but in immaculate condition. It has 2 full magazines down the barrel. That means that this gun has had 60 rounds through it since Red Jacket built it.

One of the things that makes this firearm so incredibly unique is the fact that the original Yugoslavian military issue barrel was utilized. The United States Department of Defense no longer allows the import of functioning barrels to be included with parts kits imported into the U.S. Barrels made in the U.S. are offered and often included with parts kits like these - the trouble is that the U.S. made barrels pale in comparison to a military-issue quality barrel.

Since the factory barrel was used, Red Jacket pinned their inert silencer onto the muzzle of the firearm, thus making it NFA compliant. Due to that, this gun can transfer to a regular FFL and no $200 tax stamp is needed as it is not considered an SBR (short barrel rifle).

This is from my personal collection, and does not require doing paperwork as long as you have a valid Texas Drivers license. I will also write a bill of sale to you for your records.

Also, I just wanted to add that this gun has very little kick to it. I was really surprised it was so comfortable to shoot.

Don't miss your opportunity to own this M92 krink built by Red Jacket Firearms.

postcontent:
Up for sale is an extremely cool Polish PPS-43c ..This gun was manufactured in Radom,Poland by Pioneer Arms Corp..I purchased it new and have fired less than 100 rounds through it..Its a blast to shoot and is very accurate.Great piece to own!!..This gun has no issues and works and functions flawlessly..Still looks new!! Comes with an original PPSh-41 Russian sling, 4 mags..I also have 625 rounds of Tokarev(7.62x25) ammo in ammo box...Will include all of the ammo to the purchaser of the gun for 100 bucks extra!!!!.Please email with questions..Thanks!

Specs:
PPS43-C Pistol

HISTORIC TREASURES

The history...

The PPS43 (Pistolet-Pulemet Sudaeva, model of 1943 = Sudaev submachine gun) was born as an answer for the need of a weapon that would be more compact and mobile than the PPSh-41, which was in use then by the Soviet Army. The PPSh-41 was somewhat too long to be used by tank crews, mobile recon groups and paratroopers. In late 1941, the Red Army issued a request for a new, more compact SMG. Designer Sudaev initially designed his new SMG in 1942 and it was adopted under the designation of PPS42. Next year he refined the design and this final model was designated as PPS43. This SMG was manufactured in significant numbers, with nearly 2 million PPS43 weapons manufactured between 1943 and 1946. The PPS43 is sometimes referred to as the best SMG of World War II. After WWII, it was widely exported to pro-Soviet regimes around the world and widely copied.

The PPS43 was license-produced in Poland starting in 1946.

Today…

Pioneer Arms together with, I.O. Inc., has redesigned this historical firearm to shoot from a closed bolt position. The safety is located at the front of the trigger guard. The receiver and barrel shroud are made from stamped steel. The rear sight is an L-shaped flip type and is marked for 100 and 200 meters distance. The front sight is a fixed blade. The barrel is equipped with a simple muzzle brake. This firearm is an ATF approved pistol. The stock has no function and is permanently fixed in its folded closed position.

This pistol is manufactured at the famed Radom Plant in Poland by Pioneer Arms. All parts and components are Polish made. The PPS43-C pistol comes with a curved box magazine which holds up to 35 rounds.

title: For Sale:  Mongolian recurve bow
location: Saint Paul (Midway), Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
I have for sale my Mongolian traditional recurve bow handcrafted by famous bowmaker Toth Zoltan in Hungary. I had it made in 2011. The draw length is 28 inches. Not sure what the draw weight is but it is very easy to shoot. I've shot targets from over 30 yards and it is a very comfortable bow. Springtime is here and there are FREE outdoor archery ranges in the Twin Cities! This is a great opportunity for those who want a practical and reliable, truly traditional & instinctive shooting bow away from the techy modern bows that most people use today.

Bow Description:
The Mongolian style is a more than 1000 year-old-style. The Mongolian bows are always symmetric bows. They have "string-pads" for stopping the string rapidly after the shot. Thus the arrow earns a higher impulse, and a higher starting velocity than at the other bows, which have no string-pads.

The bows are composite bows. They consist of 3 main parts:
The 2 end-parts, which are made out of wood (normally ash, cherry and pear) the hilt and the reflex-curves, which are made out of fiberglass covered by cow-leather.

The string is made out of "Dacron"-which is a stretchable plastic, and "Kevlar" for the string bandage. At the hilt, they have a wooden plate, to make the bow's surface smoother for the arrow.


I will include for FREE:
1. Thumb ring
2. Forearm guard
3. Archery glove
2. Mongolian style leather quiver with whatever wooden arrows that are left (most have been broken or lost)

$150 cash. Price is firm. Pick up in Saint Paul.
